{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"reasoning","text":"**Refining position mapping**\n\nI'm exploring how to compute a sorted position map, possibly by using a utility function like build_tensor_sorted_position_map. It might be easier to compute using the sorted index list since position can be derived from original indices, but that would take O(n) time. I’m thinking about asserting this with a map list. I also need to add a test invocation to the main function list and update both the IQ line and the ledger with new queue items, especially inspecting the top lines around 266-275 for precision."}}
